*** The noun or pronoun that comes at the beginning
of a sentence is called the "subject." ***

*** Be is a "verb." Almost all English sentences have a
subject and a verb. ***

Grammar is easy.
My name is John.
My books are on the table.
My brother is 21 years old.
The weather is cold today.
The windows are open.
My money is in my wallet.
Mr. Smith is a teacher.
Mrs. Lee is at home now.
The sun is bright today.
Tom is at home right now.
My roommates are from Chicago.
My sister is a student in high school.
My notebooks are on the table.
My book's on my desk.
The teacher's in class.
